    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><div n="1" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/>
                Proscaenium </ab></div><div n="2" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/> columnis <supplied reason="lost">e</supplied>t marmoribus </ab></div><div n="3" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/> ex HS <expan><abbr>CC</abbr><ex>ducentibus milibus</ex></expan> a Marcio Vitale itemque ex HS <expan><abbr>CCC</abbr><ex>trecentibus milibus</ex></expan> a Iunio Galba in eam rem </ab></div><div n="4" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/> <supplied reason="lost">datis item</supplied> <lb n="2"/><supplied reason="lost">tetrastylis</supplied> lac<supplied reason="lost">u</supplied>nar<supplied reason="lost">um</supplied> </ab></div><div n="5" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/> <expan><abbr>pec</abbr><ex>unia</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>publ</abbr><ex>ica</ex></expan> exornatum dedicatum est <expan><abbr>L</abbr><ex>ucio</ex></expan> Hedio Rufo <supplied reason="lost">Lo</supplied>lliano Avito </ab></div><div n="6" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/> proco<expan><ex>n</ex><abbr>s</abbr><ex>ule</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>C</abbr><ex>aio</ex></expan> Vibio Gallione Clau</ab></div><div n="7" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/>dio Seve<supplied reason="lost">ro</supplied> <expan><abbr>leg</abbr><ex>ato</ex></expan>
            </ab></div></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Blöcke vom Architrav der untersten Ordnung der vorspringenden Ädikulen der scaenae frons des Theaters der Stadt; über der porta regia Inschriftfeld in Form einer tabula ansata (Breite: 465 cm); Gesamtlänge der Inschrift: ca. 30 m. (B): Di Vita, AE 1990: aedicula III: itemque ex CCC; Caputo: aedicula III: ex HS CCC a Marcio Vitale; Caputo, AE 1951: porta regia: [--- una cum] lac[u]na; Guey: porta regia: [legatis item tetrastylo? novo? in] lac[u]na; AE 1952: porta regia: [legatis item tetrastylo? novo? in?] lacuna; IRT: porta regia: [---]lac[---]; [---]na[---]. Datierung: Statthalterschaft des L. Hedius Rufus: 157/158 oder 158/159 n. Chr. Parts were found reused in the cavea as steps.</p>
            </div>
